  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div xml:id="AN147.2-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">celavuṇarttiya tōḻikkut talaimakaḷ colliyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">What SHE said to the confidante who informed [her] of [his] going.</p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="AN147.2">
            <lg type="edition">
              <l>ōṅkumalaic cilampiṟ piṭavuṭaṉ malarnta</l>
              <l>vēṅkai veṟittaḻai vēṟuvakut taṉṉa</l>
              <l>vūṉpoti yaviḻāk kōṭṭukirk kuruḷai</l>
              <l>mūṉṟuṭa ṉīṉṟa muḻaṅkā niḻatta</l>
              <l>tuṟukal viṭaraḷaip piṇavuppaci kūrnteṉap</l>
              <l>poṟikiḷa ruḻuvaip pēḻvā yēṟṟai</l>
              <l>yaṟukōṭ ṭuḻaimā ṉāṇkura lokku</l>
              <l>neṟipaṭu kavalaiya nirampā nīḷiṭai</l>
              <l>veḷḷi vītiyaip pōla naṉṟuñ</l>
              <l>celavayarn ticiṉāl yāṉē palapulan</l>
              <l>tuṇṇā vuyakkamō ṭuyircelac cāayt</l>
              <l>tōḷun tolkaviṉ ṟolaiyā nāḷum</l>
              <l>pirintōr peyarviṟ kiraṅki</l>
              <l>maruntupiṟi tiṉimaiyi ṉiruntumiṉai yalaṉē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <l>Me, let me prepare for departure indeed, (10a-c)</l>
                <l>easy like on a silver street, (9)</l>
                <l>on the endless long ways that have crossroads coming in on the path, (8)</l>
                <l>where the stag with horns broken is similar to a man, (7)</l>
                <l>[broken] by the large-mouthed male of the tiger with shining spots, (6)</l>
                <l>because [its] female’s hunger was increasing in the cave in the thick stones (5)</l>
                <l>that is reduced to not roaring, that has given birth to three at a time, (4)</l>
                <l>young ones with curved claws that do not come out of [their] sheaths, (3)</l>
                <l>who are like the perfumed foliage of the kino tree differently arranged (2)</l>
                <l>that flower together with the Piṭavu on the side of the high mountain, (1)</l>
                <l rend="indent4">I, being much vexed (10d)</l>
                <l>not eating, being exhausted from distress, so that my life will go, (11)</l>
                <l>[but] without that the old beauty of [my] shoulders is lost, daily (12)</l>
                <l>pining for the return of him who has parted [from me], (13)</l>
                <l>and [still] existing, because of the sweetness of the remedy that is different, I am not despairing. (14)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
